div.p:
Trans 29.12.93. To proof.
See also J. Moore to M, 12 October 1866. On 12 October 1866 the Under Secretary, J. Moore, minuted M 'to fill up the blanks in the prefixed slate; which he will then return to this office.' M replied on 15 October: 'Request complied with' and Moore then sent M's statement of authorities to the Commissioners of Audit on 3 January 1867 with the request that they return it to the Chief Secretary's Department. On 10 January the Commissioners replied to the request: 'The Return is correct with the exception of the following items out of Contingent Votes in which our Books differ with it.
ItemNo of authorityAmount authorisedAmount expendedBalancePlants & Seeds109£100£100—"4363.10.03.2.08Forage187120116.6.13.11 Cancelled £3.10.0Transit Expenses3483533.19.81.0.4Water Supply40415087.10.562.9.7 M was duly asked to 'point out in what respect the Balances on his Books differ from those on the Books of the Commissioner of Audit' and he replied on 21 January: 'The discrepancies between the balances contained in the books of the Audit commissioners & those of my department arose through the Commissioners having counted half pennies which had been struck out by the Treasury department (Auth. 187 & 104) An account charged to Auth. 348 has as yet not been paid, which causes another difference, and a clerical error in my Department gave rise to a discrepancy of 3/ in the authority for purchase of plants.'
